{#
  ============================================================================
  TEMPLATE: careplan_fsh.twig
  ============================================================================
  PURPOSE
    Generates a FSH CarePlan instance (base FHIR R4 — no additional EU profile)
    plus zero or more FSH Goal instances for each goal linked to the plan.
    This is the only template in the project that emits Goal instances as
    secondary FSH output appended after the primary instance's text.div.

  PROFILE CONFORMANCE
    CarePlan : base FHIR R4 CarePlan (no additional profile)
    Goal     : base FHIR R4 Goal (no additional profile)
    Fixed elements:
      status       = #active
      intent       = #plan
      category     = $sct#734163000 "Care plan (record artifact)"

  MULTI-INSTANCE OUTPUT STRUCTURE
    The %%FSH%% section emits:
      1. One CarePlan instance (registered via setInstance())
      2. Zero or more Goal instances (one per entry in `goals`; NOT registered
         via setInstance() — direct id interpolation used)
    The Goal instances appear after the CarePlan's text.div, still within
    the %%FSH%% section. SUSHI processes all instances regardless of order.

  THREE-COLUMN HTML TABLE
    Column 1 — Activity description (preferred term or display)
    Column 2 — Care plan start date (pill badge or "-")
    Column 3 — Clinical reason for the care plan

  doNotPerform — ROW TRUNCATION FLAG
    When `careplan.activity.doNotPerform` is non-empty, the activity is marked
    as not to be performed:
      * activity.detail.doNotPerform = true
    In this case, HTML cells 2 and 3 (start date and reason) are NOT emitted.
    The HTML row will contain only cell 1 (the activity name), producing a
    row with fewer cells than the 3-column header. Callers using this flag
    should ensure their stylesheet handles short rows gracefully.

  RAW CODE VALUES — CALLER SUPPLIES # PREFIX
    Two FSH rules receive values without a `#` prefix in the template:
      * activity.detail.status = {{ careplan.status }}
      * activity.detail.kind   = {{ careplan.kind }}
    The fallback values DO use the `#` prefix:
      * activity.detail.status = #unknown
      * activity.detail.kind   = #Appointment
    This means the caller must supply status and kind values WITH the leading
    `#` (e.g. `#not-started`, `#Appointment`) when providing data. Omitting
    the `#` will produce invalid FSH. This is unlike most other templates
    where the `#` is embedded in the template itself.

  ACTIVITY DETAIL DESCRIPTION — CONDITIONAL
    When `careplan.activity.preferredTerm` is non-empty:
      - FSH: `* activity.detail.description = "{{ careplan.activity.preferredTerm }}"`
      - HTML td 1: preferredTerm value
    When empty:
      - No `activity.detail.description` rule is emitted
      - HTML td 1: `careplan.activity.display` value
    This means description is only set on the FHIR resource when a preferred
    term is available.

  CARE PLAN CATEGORY — COMMENTED-OUT ALTERNATIVE
    A commented-out FSH `//` line documents a previously considered but
    incorrect category code:
      // wrong: http://…/care-plan-category#assess-plan "Assessment and Plan"
    The correct code used is $sct#734163000 "Care plan (record artifact)".
    FSH `//` comments survive into the SUSHI output (unlike Twig `{ # # }`).

  GOALS — TWO-PASS PATTERN
    Goals are processed in two separate loops over the `goals` array:

    PASS 1 (before text.div) — HTML accumulation + FSH goal references:
      Each goal contributes:
        1. A `goal[+] = Reference(urn:uuid:{{ g.instanceid }})` FSH rule on
           the CarePlan.
        2. An `<li>` element appended to the `got` accumulator variable.
      The `| escape` filter is applied to `g.description` when building the
      `<li>` HTML: `g.description | escape`. This prevents XSS by converting
      special characters (`<`, `>`, `&`, etc.) to HTML entities before they
      are embedded in the markup string.
      When any goals are present (`got` is non-empty), a second HTML table row
      is added below the activity row:
        Row 2: `<ul>` + escaped goal list + `</ul>` | raw (td 1), empty td 2, empty td 3
      The `| raw` on `addHTML_td("…" ~ got | raw ~ "…")` prevents double-
      escaping — the individual items were already escaped by `| escape`, so
      the assembled HTML string must be passed through raw.

    PASS 2 (after text.div) — Goal FSH instances:
      A second `{% for g in goals %}` loop emits a complete FSH Goal instance
      per goal:
        Instance: Instance-Goal-{{ g.instanceid }}
        InstanceOf: Goal
        Title: "{{ g.title }}"
        Description: "{{ g.description }}"
        Usage: #inline
        * id = "{{ g.instanceid }}"
        * lifecycleStatus = #active
        * description.text = "{{ g.description }}"
        * subject = Reference(urn:uuid:{{ patient.instanceid }}) "{{ patient.name }}"
        {{ g.fsh | raw }}
      These Goal instances:
        - Are NOT registered via setInstance() — direct id interpolation used.
        - Will not appear in the twigit() return array.
        - Carry `g.fsh | raw` — a pre-built FSH string for additional goal
          properties (e.g. target, note, expressedBy) produced upstream.
        - Are appended after the CarePlan's text.div, still within %%FSH%%.

  NARRATIVE — FULL HEADED TABLE (Pattern 2)
    Both emitHEAD() and emitHTML() flushed inside text.div.
    CSS class: `hl7__ips first25` (first column constrained to ~25% width).

  `| escape` / `| raw` PAIR PATTERN
    This is the only template in the project that uses `| escape` on user-
    supplied content before embedding it in an HTML string accumulator.
    The pattern is:
      1. `| escape` on individual values when building the accumulator string
         → converts `<`, `>`, `&` etc. to HTML entities (XSS-safe)
      2. `| raw` when emitting the assembled string
         → prevents Twig from double-escaping the already-safe entities
    This pattern should be applied wherever user-supplied content is embedded
    in raw HTML string accumulators across the project.

  CONTEXT VARIABLES
  ┌──────────────────────────────────────┬──────────┬────────────────────────────────────────────┐
  │ Variable                             │ Type     │ Description                                │
  ├──────────────────────────────────────┼──────────┼────────────────────────────────────────────┤
  │ instanceid                           │ string   │ Unique resource id for the CarePlan.       │
  │ patient.instanceid                   │ string   │ UUID of the Patient resource.              │
  │ patient.name                         │ string   │ Full display name.                         │
  │ careplan.status                      │ string?  │ FSH activity status code WITH `#` prefix   │
  │                                      │          │ (e.g. "#not-started"). When empty,         │
  │                                      │          │ `#unknown` is used as fallback.            │
  │ careplan.kind                        │ string?  │ FSH activity kind code WITH `#` prefix     │
  │                                      │          │ (e.g. "#Appointment"). When empty,         │
  │                                      │          │ `#Appointment` is used as fallback.        │
  │ careplan.activity.system             │ string   │ CodeSystem URI for the activity code.      │
  │ careplan.activity.code               │ string?  │ Activity concept code (conditional).       │
  │ careplan.activity.display            │ string   │ Activity display text; used in HTML td 1   │
  │                                      │          │ when preferredTerm is absent.              │
  │ careplan.activity.preferredTerm      │ string?  │ Preferred display override; when non-empty,│
  │                                      │          │ sets activity.detail.description AND       │
  │                                      │          │ populates HTML td 1.                       │
  │ careplan.activity.doNotPerform       │ string?  │ When non-empty, emits doNotPerform = true  │
  │                                      │          │ and suppresses HTML cells 2 and 3.         │
  │ careplan.start                       │ string?  │ ISO 8601 care plan start date.             │
  │ careplan.reason.system               │ string   │ CodeSystem URI for the reason code.        │
  │ careplan.reason.code                 │ string?  │ Clinical reason concept code (conditional).│
  │ careplan.reason.display              │ string   │ Reason display text for HTML td 3.         │
  │ goals                                │ object[] │ Array of goal objects (may be empty).      │
  │   [n].instanceid                     │ string   │   UUID for the Goal resource.              │
  │   [n].title                          │ string   │   Goal title (FSH Title keyword).          │
  │   [n].description                    │ string   │   Goal description; | escape applied in    │
  │                                      │          │   HTML; used raw in FSH description.text. │
  │   [n].fsh                            │ string?  │   Pre-built FSH string for additional      │
  │                                      │          │   Goal properties; injected with \| raw.   │
  └──────────────────────────────────────┴──────────┴────────────────────────────────────────────┘

  CODESYSTEMS REFERENCED
    $sct — 734163000 "Care plan (record artifact)" (category)
    Activity, reason codesystem URIs — caller-supplied

  AUTHOR   KH
  SINCE    2025-09-10
  ============================================================================
#}

%%FSH%% {# ── Section marker required by the FSH pre-processor ─────────────── #}

Instance: {{ setInstance("Instance-CarePlan-" ~ instanceid) }}
InstanceOf: CarePlan
Title: "CarePlan"
Description: "CarePlan"
Usage: #inline

* id = "{{ instanceid }}"

{# HEAD bag: three-column table header #}
{{ addHEAD_tr() }}
{{ addHEAD_th("Active Planned Care / Goals") }}
{{ addHEAD_th("Start Date") }}
{{ addHEAD_th("Reason") }}
{{ addHEAD_trend() -}}

{{ addHTML_tr() }}

{# Fixed status and intent #}
* status = #active
* intent = #plan

* subject = Reference(urn:uuid:{{ patient.instanceid }}) "{{ patient.name }}"

{#
  Fixed category: SNOMED "Care plan (record artifact)".
  The FSH // comment below documents a previously considered (incorrect) code.
  FSH // comments survive into the SUSHI output unlike Twig {# #} comments.
#}
// wrong: http://terminology.hl7.org/CodeSystem/care-plan-category#assess-plan "Assessment and Plan"
* category.coding = $sct#734163000 "Care plan (record artifact)"

{#
  ── Activity status ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  ⚠ careplan.status must include the `#` prefix (e.g. "#not-started").
  The template does not add `#` — unlike most other coded fields.
  Fallback: #unknown when status is empty.
#}
{% if careplan.status is empty %}
* activity.detail.status = #unknown
{% else %}
* activity.detail.status = {{ careplan.status }}
{% endif %}

{# Activity code (conditional) #}
{% if careplan.activity.code is not empty %}
* activity.detail.code.coding = {{ careplan.activity.system }}#{{ careplan.activity.code }} "{{ careplan.activity.display }}"
{% endif %}

{#
  ── TD 1: activity description ───────────────────────────────────────────────
  When preferredTerm is non-empty: sets activity.detail.description AND uses it
  in HTML. When empty: HTML uses display but no description rule is emitted.
#}
{% if careplan.activity.preferredTerm is not empty %}
* activity.detail.description = "{{ careplan.activity.preferredTerm }}"
{{ addHTML_td(careplan.activity.preferredTerm) }}
{% else %}
{{ addHTML_td(careplan.activity.display) }}
{% endif %}

{#
  ── Activity kind ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  ⚠ careplan.kind must include the `#` prefix (e.g. "#Appointment").
  Fallback: #Appointment when kind is empty.
#}
{% if careplan.kind is empty %}
* activity.detail.kind = #Appointment
{% else %}
* activity.detail.kind = {{ careplan.kind }}
{% endif %}

{#
  ── doNotPerform gate ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  When set, marks the activity as not to be performed and skips HTML cells
  2 and 3. The row will have fewer cells than the 3-column header.
  When absent, normal start date and reason rules + HTML cells 2 and 3 follow.
#}
{% if careplan.activity.doNotPerform is not empty %}
* activity.detail.doNotPerform = true
{# HTML cells 2 and 3 are suppressed when doNotPerform is set #}

{% else %}

{# TD 2: start date (conditional) #}
{% if careplan.start is not empty %}
* period.start = "{{ careplan.start }}"
{{ addHTML_tdnb(careplan.start|date('d-M-Y')) }}
{% else %}
{{ addHTML_tdnb("-") }}
{% endif %}

{# TD 3: clinical reason (conditional) #}
{% if careplan.reason.code is empty %}
{{ addHTML_td("-") }}
{% else %}
* activity.detail.reasonCode = {{ careplan.reason.system }}#{{ careplan.reason.code }} "{{ careplan.reason.display }}"
{{ addHTML_td(careplan.reason.display) }}
{% endif %}

{% endif %} {# doNotPerform #}

{{ addHTML_trend() -}}

{#
  ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  GOALS — PASS 1: FSH references on CarePlan + HTML list accumulation
  Builds:
    - goal[+] References on the CarePlan
    - `got` HTML list string using | escape on each description (XSS-safe)
  ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#}
{% set got = "" %}
{% for g in goals %}
* goal[+] = Reference(urn:uuid:{{ g.instanceid }})
{#
  | escape converts special chars to HTML entities before embedding in the
  accumulator string, preventing XSS if descriptions contain < > & etc.
#}
{% set got = got ~ "<li>" ~ g.description | escape ~ "</li>" %}
{% endfor %}

{#
  Optional second HTML row for goals.
  | raw on the assembled `got` string prevents double-escaping — items were
  already escaped individually above. The empty cells fill columns 2 and 3.
#}
{% if got is not empty %}
{{ addHTML_tr() }}
{{ addHTML_td("<ul>" ~ got | raw ~ "</ul>") }}
{{ addHTML_td("") }}
{{ addHTML_td("") }}
{{ addHTML_trend() -}}
{% endif %}

{#
  ── FHIR narrative — full headed table (Pattern 2) ──────────────────────────
  CSS class: hl7__ips first25 (first column constrained to ~25% width).
#}
* text.status = #generated
* text.div    = """
<div xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
<table class="hl7__ips first25">{{ emitHEAD() | raw }}{{ emitHTML() | raw }}</table>
</div>
"""

{#
  ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  GOALS — PASS 2: Goal FSH instances (appended after CarePlan text.div)
  One Goal instance per entry in `goals`. All within the %%FSH%% section.
  NOT registered via setInstance() — direct id interpolation used.
  g.fsh | raw injects pre-built FSH properties produced upstream by the caller.
  ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#}
{% for g in goals %}
Instance: Instance-Goal-{{ g.instanceid }}
InstanceOf: Goal
Title: "{{ g.title }}"
Description: "{{ g.description}}"
Usage: #inline
* id               = "{{ g.instanceid }}"
* lifecycleStatus  = #active
* description.text = "{{ g.description}}"
* subject          = Reference(urn:uuid:{{ patient.instanceid }}) "{{ patient.name }}"

{# Pre-built FSH string for additional Goal properties (targets, notes, etc.) #}
{{ g.fsh | raw }}

{% endfor %}

%%HEAD%% {# ── Section marker required by the FSH pre-processor ─────────────── #}
{{ emitHEAD() | raw }}

%%HTML%% {# ── Section marker required by the FSH pre-processor ─────────────── #}
{{ emitHTML() | raw }}
